.docname {Importing external libraries}
.include {docs}

The **`.include`** function, previously seen in [*Including other LayerDocs files*](including-other-layerdocs-files.qd), can also import external **libraries**.

When you download LayerDocs or build it via `distZip`, the `lib/qd` directory contains utility libraries written in LayerDocs itself.

.filetree
    - layerdocs
      - lib
        - qd
          - lib.qd
          - ...
      - bin
        - layerdocs.jar

You can import `.qd` files into a LayerDocs project via `.include {name}`, without the file extension.

For example, to import `paper.qd`, use `.include {paper}`.

> Note: Unlike `.include {path}`, this approach only loads declared symbols without appending Markdown content from the file.

> Tip: The default library directory is `<install directory>/lib/qd`. You can override this via the command-line option `-l` or `--libs`.
